        <title type="html"><![CDATA[Mirror of the soul]]></title>
        <published>2022-12-14T23:10:00+08:00</published>
        <updated>2022-12-14T23:10:00+08:00</updated>
        <id>urn:uuid:4bc880e0-7c9b-5769-394f-fad9fba96adc</id>
            <author>
                <name>Zoë C.</name>
            </author>
        <summary type="html"><![CDATA[If translation means re-creating the inner experiences of reading, we encounter a fundamental indeterminacy when translating classical texts. The timespan that makes a classical text classic also obliterates what is fleeting in time. However, among the ephemeral existences, it is the subtle mental realities that we aim to re-create by translation.]]></summary>
